JSON_SCHEMA_BODY:
Return a JSON array where EACH DEVICE gets its own object with complete configuration:

Example for "Configure OSPF area 0 between R1 (router-id 1.1.1.1) and R2 (router-id 2.2.2.2)":
[
  {
    "device_name": "R1",
    "protocol": "OSPF",
    "configuration_mode_commands": [
      "configure terminal",
      "router ospf 1",
      "router-id 1.1.1.1",
      "network 10.0.0.0 0.0.0.255 area 0",
      "exit"
    ],
    "intent": [
      {
        "type": "adjacency",
        "endpoints": [
          {"role": "router", "id": "R1"},
          {"role": "router", "id": "R2"}
        ],
        "properties": {
          "description": "OSPF neighbor relationship in area 0"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "device_name": "R2",
    "protocol": "OSPF",
    "configuration_mode_commands": [
      "configure terminal",
      "router ospf 1",
      "router-id 2.2.2.2",
      "network 10.0.0.0 0.0.0.255 area 0",
      "exit"
    ],
    "intent": [
      {
        "type": "adjacency",
        "endpoints": [
          {"role": "router", "id": "R2"},
          {"role": "router", "id": "R1"}
        ],
        "properties": {
          "description": "OSPF neighbor relationship in area 0"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
]

IMPORTANT: 
- Generate a SEPARATE object for EACH device mentioned in the goal
- Return ONLY this JSON array format
- No explanatory text
- No markdown code fences
